Test 2 — Create Booking
POST http://localhost:8080/api/bookings
Authorization: Bearer <user_token>
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "spotId": "<spot_id_from_admin_service>",
    "vehicleNumber": "MH12AB1234",
    "vehicleType": "FOUR_WHEELER",
    "entryGateId": "<gate_id_from_admin_service>"
}
To get spotId and gateId — run these in MySQL Workbench:
sqlSELECT id, spot_code, is_occupied FROM parking_spots LIMIT 5;
SELECT id, gate_code, gate_type FROM entry_exit_gates LIMIT 5;

Test 3 — Get Booking by ID
GET http://localhost:8080/api/bookings/<booking_id>
Authorization: Bearer <user_token>

Test 4 — Get My Bookings (Paginated)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/bookings/my-bookings?page=0&size=10
Authorization: Bearer <user_token>

Test 5 — Process Vehicle Exit
POST http://localhost:8080/api/bookings/<booking_id>/exit
Authorization: Bearer <user_token>
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "exitGateId": "<gate_id>"
}
This will:

Calculate fee based on duration
Mark spot as available again
Update booking to COMPLETED
Publish Kafka event (if Kafka running)


Test 6 — Cancel Booking (create new booking first)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/bookings/<booking_id>/cancel
Authorization: Bearer <user_token>

